about.description: libxfoil is a library to analyze the aerodynamics of 2-dimensional airfoi sections programmatically using the Xfoil aerodynamics engine.

name: libxfoil
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "libxfoil" %}
{% set version = "1.0" %}

package:
    name: {{ name }}
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    url: https://github.com/montagdude/{{ name }}/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: "1e251aac259bac84aa5be318ae62a496b705c625f0e54c44af230494904858ac"

build:
    number: 0
    skip: true  # [py<36 or win]

requirements:
    build:
        - {{ compiler("c") }}              # [unix]
        - {{ compiler("fortran") }}        # [unix]
        - {{ compiler("m2w64_c") }}        # [win]
        - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}  # [win]
        - vs2015_win-64                    # [win]
        - cmake
        - swig
    host:
        - python
    run:
        - python

test:
  imports:
    - xfoil_interface

about:
    home: https://github.com/montagdude/libxfoil
    license: GPL-2
    license_family: GPL
    license_file: LICENSE
    summary: libxfoil (xfoil + python bindings)
    description: libxfoil is a library to analyze the aerodynamics of 2-dimensional airfoi
                 sections programmatically using the Xfoil aerodynamics engine. 
    doc_url: https://github.com/montagdude/libxfoil
    dev_url: https://github.com/montagdude/libxfoil

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - looooo
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.14
